			<description><![CDATA[<p>
Retail Manager-</p>
<p>
<strong>About the Job:</strong><br />
Zane Prep INC provides supplemental STEM enrichment courses in independently owned school campuses, retail store campuses, and teacher-owned virtual campuses. Its flagship product, Zane Math K-8, takes the world&rsquo;s best Asian and Western math programs to a new level by customizing the Curriculum for each student. We provide retail offerings in three specific areas: STEM Enrichment, Homework Center, and Math Tutoring.</p>
<p>
<strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Provide customer service by presenting pricing, preparing sales, and processing transactions</li>
<li>
Maintain knowledge of current sales and promotions, policies regarding payment, exchanges, and store security</li>
<li>
Ensure employees effectively follow company standards, policies, procedures and implement awareness of Zane Prep products</li>
<li>
Initiate, develop and support store events, sales driving activities and outreach programs to build Zane Prep awareness and increase sales</li>
<li>
Greet customers in a timely, professional and engaging manner</li>
<li>
Deliver excellent customer service and support that inspires repeat visits and expands our customer base</li>
<li>
Possess the ability to manage multiple employees and are able to recognize a challenge and identify a solution</li>
<li>
Outgoing personality that is able to effectively communicate with both parents and kids</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Preferences:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Ability to work effectively in a diverse office setting.</li>
<li>
Maintain organizational skills to manage workflow and establish a harmonious and productive environment.  </li>
<li>
Skill in accurately analyzing information, situations, and procedures to define problems and formulate conclusions.  </li>
<li>
Excellent communication and interpersonal skills.</li>
<li>
Self-motivated to complete tasks that are assigned.</li>
<li>
Willingness to work in a team environment and help out where ever asked.</li>
<li>
Have experience working with kids - either coaching, student teaching, baby sitting, or in any other professional capacity.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Skills, Abilities and Other Requirements:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Excellent customer service skills</li>
<li>
Ability to recognize and execute selling opportunities</li>
<li>
Good communication and organizational skills</li>
<li>
Ability to multi-task in a fast paced environment</li>
<li>
Ability to take initiative to complete tasks and solve problems</li>
<li>
Ability to meet deadlines</li>
<li>
Ability to manage time and prioritize</li>
<li>
Must be willing to reach out to community to get greater involvement and traffic directed to the store.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Minimum Qualifications:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
High school diploma or equivalency required. Have customer service experience, demonstrated human relation and effective communication skills also required. Applicants must demonstrate the potential ability to perform the essential functions of the job as outlined in the position description.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Contact Us:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Email your resume to careers@zaneprep.com</li>
</ul>
